			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>What if we could add augs to spells ?</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>In addition to normal focus items what if we could use our reaserch skills to augment spells with aditional effects. Soe seems to stipulate that spells for us = weapons for mele so this makes sense.<br />
<br />
<br />
Strike through scroll combined with a specific spell would give a certain percentage of damage to slip past resists 15% 25% 35% on a full resist <br />
<br />
Mana Reduction scoll could give a additional 10% 20% and 30% reduction to the spells base mana cost. This would actually reduce the mana cost on the spell so you need less mana to cast it<br />
<br />
Spell haste scroll adds a addition haste mod on spells cast times that stacks with other spell haste<br />
<br />
Confusion scroll reducess aggro on nukes that it is combined to.<br />
<br />
how it can work is you can unmem a spell and get a scroll of that spell back and combine it with a augmentation scroll to add a effect to it.<br />
<br />
<br />
comments ?</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
