		<!-- message -->
		<div>lol?<br />
<br />
Sorry, but I think Sony sufficiently clusterfucked the implementation of <i>regular</i> focus effects already.<br />
<br />
We really don't need another 10 effects to hunt down in order to reach median performance.<br />
<br />
I appreciate the interest in more uses for skills and the impetus for questing/research, etc.  But I think we are already balanced with melee in terms of our reliance on equipment for power advancement.  Between the implementation of &quot;Flowing Thought&quot; items, focus effects, clicky effects (Concussions legs, Mana Regen buff from Quarm shoulders or similar effects) and then the standard need for +Mana and +HP gear we have plenty of motivation to seek out upgrades.<br />
<br />
Also, the idea seems a bit redundant with what already exists in game.<br />
<br />
My opinion is that they need to develop something by way of expendable &quot;scrolls&quot; that are made with the research skill.  Make them either charged items or whatever and maybe add a recast timer to items flagged as scrolls.  This could be a way to allow players to fabricate magical supplements without being overpowered.  Similar to alchemy for potions and such.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
