	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Ok there is 2 separate ideas here one for the the ability to augument current spells and one to customize certain spells with additional effects.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
AUGUMENTED SPELL EFFECTS<br />
<br />
Reduced cast times for one specific spell<br />
Reduced Recast timer for a specific spell<br />
Reduced base mana cost for one specific spell<br />
Strike through effect on a specific spell (a minimum % of damage on a full resist will hit)<br />
Crit mod increase on a specific spell<br />
<br />
These augmented effects should stack with existing focus effects increasing both sustained dps and burst dps <br />
<br />
Auguments should be usable on spells to level 70<br />
<br />
I can see this possibly being a huge boost to sustained dps using lower level spells.<br />
<br />
Reducing cast times on lower spells to 1 sec and haveing them hit for 600 base damage to 1200 with cits  in  conjunture with a enhanced resist mod and a enhanced mana cost would make sustained group dps where we should be.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
CUSTOMIZED SPELL EFFECTS<br />
The second idea is to be able to split our spells to there base effects and rearrange them to have more functions or utility without becoming unbalanced..<br />
<br />
<br />
Customized spell effecets shuold probably be level capped for the damage part of the spell to a certain level and a certain set of spells that are allowed to be ripped apart for base effects to be used to make new spells<br />
<br />
Shadowstep<br />
Disintigrate<br />
Nukes up to a certain dps level maybe not the big nukes <br />
AE spells<br />
<br />
<br />
Option 1 Single target, Area Effect, Self and resist type<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Option 2 Damage or Base effect could be pulled from a existing spell along with base mana cost<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Option 3 Secondary Effect<br />
<br />
The secondary effect will and additional mana cost with effects already existing on our spells<br />
<br />
Allowable effects<br />
Snare + 75mana<br />
Stun +80 mana<br />
Root +50 mana<br />
Lure base +150 mana<br />
<br />
<br />
Im sure they could run a program to see the possible self combinations that would be allowed and limit unbalancing combinations for being made<br />
<br />
<br />
Some spells that could be made<br />
<br />
Directional shadowstep<br />
<br />
Targeted shadowstep + root<br />
<br />
For PVP wiz<br />
Nuke then Abscond in same spell<br />
<br />
Root rain spell with no damage<br />
<br />
AE knockback with root<br />
